# CODEOWNERS for the Fifty monorepo.
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews when a PR touches the
# listed paths. The `bin/` scripts and the CI workflow definitions
# are the two places where a bad change has blast-radius across every
# theme, so we require an explicit owner sign-off before merge.
#
# Format: <path glob>  <space-separated owners>
#
# References:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/
#     customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: the repository owner reviews anything not covered below.
*                           @nickhamze

# Tooling & CI: changes here affect every theme + every contributor.
/bin/                       @nickhamze
/.github/                   @nickhamze
/pyproject.toml             @nickhamze
/requirements-dev.txt       @nickhamze
/tests/                     @nickhamze
/.githooks/                 @nickhamze
